Ingredients.2: 1 (16 ounce) package pork sausage (such as Owens® Original)

Ingredients.5: 1 (10 ounce) can diced tomatoes with green chile peppers (such as RO*TEL®)

Ingredients.6: 1 (12 ounce) package frozen chopped broccoli, thawed

Ingredients.8: 1 (10.75 ounce) can  cream of celery soup

Ingredients.9: 1 (32 ounce) package frozen bite-size potato nuggets (such as Tater Tots®)

Ingredients.10: 1 pinch ground black and red pepper blend (such as McCormick® Hot Shot®), or to taste

Directions.1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Spray a 2-quart baking dish with cooking spray.

Directions.2: Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook and stir sausage in the hot skillet until browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes; drain and discard grease. Add onion and garlic; cook and stir until onion is softened, 5 to 10 minutes.

Directions.3: Mix tomatoes with green chile peppers, broccoli, Mexican cheese blend, and cream of celery soup into sausage mixture; spread into the prepared baking dish. Arrange potato nuggets over sausage mixture; season with pepper.

Directions.4: Bake in the preheated oven until cheese is bubbling and potato nuggets are slightly brown, about 45 minutes.
